\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\item Zaid has a non-calculator method for working out if a number is a multiple of 11.
He shows his method for the number 919 281.

\begin{parts}
    \item Subtract and add alternately the digits in the number. \hfill $9 - 1 + 9 - 2 + 8 - 1 = 22$
    \item Check if the answer is a multiple of 11. \hfill $22 = 2 \times 11$
    \item As 22 is a multiple of 11 then 919 281 is a multiple of 11.
\end{parts}

